			<div class="content" id="post-content-2419037">
									

<p>+1</p>
<p>This is sooooo damn good.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;Praise</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I'm not sure if I'm just a sucker for this style of writing, but I just love the &quot;cognitive dissonance&quot;/aphasiatic tone here and I think you do it so well. It really feels like every word was perfectly chosen. I put this in the same category as <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1877">SCP-1877</a> which, believe me, is high praise from me.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We were wondering how we were going to finish bleeding for Ross without the knife when the rest of us started developing pains in our left side.<br />
&#8230;<br />
He just started prematurely regurgitating his blood and wood pulp into the casket&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I just really love the word choice here. You show how our bystander has anomalously learned the ritual, even to the point where he and the family are thrown off when it doesn't go according to plan.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>He reached over to the tabernacle and opened it up to reveal a hidden camera! Then, he went over to Aunt Maureen, stuck a finger up her nose and pulled out another camera! Oh my god, we were on a prank show all this time!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>You effectively turn SCP-2030 into a sort of hero here. A weird, creepy, disgusting, homicidal, hilarious hero.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This was way over the top, and you know Ross would have wanted it this way.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Also great word choice here, with the bystander just getting soooo into it!</p>
<p>The announcer's final note was great too, you captured that alien/humorous/confused/creepy tone perfectly.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I had forgotten how fun funerals are. We should have them more often.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>And you even managed to end by showing that our protagonist is still affected by the homicidal influences of SCP-2852, maybe even moreso than he would have otherwise been.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My brother Ross died a week ago in a freak accident involving a slow loris. Turns out, they're related to monkeys, and poisonous. Who knew? I never knew Ross was into slow lorises, anyway. The doctor said there was a rash of slow loris attacks recently, which is strange, because they're kinda like sloths otherwise.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is the one confusing thing about the whole skip. Is there something about the Slow Loris' I'm not getting? Or was he actually killed by a Slow Loris?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Great job! Very impressive, and much fun to read (and re-read).</p>

							</div>

								
					
